data.title: Aptiv (NYSE: APTV) reported a record quarter with $2.17 EPS, $5.21B revenue, $654M operating income, and $851M EBITDA.
data.description: Aptiv Plc reported strong third-quarter earnings, with adjusted earnings of $2.17 per share, surpassing analyst expectations of $1.82. Revenue stood at $5.21 billion, higher than the anticipated $5.09 billion, showing a 7.4% increase year over year. The company reported adjusted operating income of $654 million and adjusted EBITDA of $851 million. Adjusted operating income margin rose to 12.5% from 12.2% a year earlier, due to improved operational efficiency and cost-reduction initiatives. Net cash flow from operating activities was $584 million in Q3, compared to $499 million in the previous year. Aptiv ended the quarter with $1.64 billion in cash and total liquidity of $4.2 billion. During the quarter, the company redeemed $148 million in senior notes and repurchased 1.2 million shares for $96 million.

data.title: EQT sells Galderma shares for CHF 2.6 billion, receiving CHF 690 million. Transaction completed.
data.description: The recent sale generated total gross proceeds of around CHF 2.6 billion, with EQT gaining approximately CHF 690 million. On October 30, 2025, in Stockholm, an affiliate of EQT VIII ("EQT") concluded the transaction following earlier notifications.

data.title: Frankenmuth Insurance's Senior Director of Commercial Lines Craig Alarie retires Dec 31, 2025, after 3 decades.
data.description: In Frankenmuth, Michigan, Craig Alarie, the Senior Director of Commercial Lines for the Mid-South area, will be retiring from Frankenmuth Insurance on December 31, 2025. Having served for over 30 years, Alarie has been a significant leader in the company.

data.title: Currax Pharmaceuticals to present CONTRAVE data at ObesityWeek, showcasing 4 out of 7 studies on weight loss benefits.
data.description: At ObesityWeek, four out of seven data presentations will be showcased during a press conference, highlighting the effectiveness of CONTRAVE in aiding weight loss. This event is scheduled to take place in BRENTWOOD, Tenn., on October 28, 2025. Currax Pharmaceuticals LLC ("Currax"), a pharmaceutical company, is spearheading these presentations. The data shared will emphasize the utility of CONTRAVE in assisting individuals with weight loss.

data.title: Former NetApp CEO Dan Warmenhoven joins Secret Double Octopus's Board of Directors, leveraging his expertise to scale the company serving global enterprises and bring operational insights.
data.description: Secret Double Octopus, a prominent workforce authentication security company based in Menlo Park, California, revealed the addition of Dan Warmenhoven to their Board of Directors. Warmenhoven, known for his remarkable success in expanding technology firms and extensive background in cybersecurity, joins the board to aid SDO in meeting the rising demand from highly regulated multinational corporations. With over his years of experience, Warmenhoven provides unmatched operational knowledge to Secret Double Octopus. Previously, he held the position of CEO at NetApp for a significant period.

data.title: Eon's Digital Car Keys streamline EV rentals, offering a seamless booking experience. Users can now unlock and start cars via smartphone.
data.description: Eon, an EV mobility platform based in New York, has unveiled a revamped Eon App in 2025 to enhance the rental and driving experience for users. The updated app prioritizes control and convenience, aiming to streamline the process for EV renters. Through the redesign, Eon aims to minimize any potential obstacles and provide a smoother booking experience, simplifying rentals significantly. As of today, customers can access and begin using any Eon vehicle by utilizing their smartphone, eliminating the need for physical keys.

data.title: Australian startup Cuttable has launched in the U.S., offering 3.1 billion AI-made ads to online stores on Meta platforms.
data.description: An Australian startup, Cuttable, employing artificial intelligence to streamline ad creation for ecommerce brands, has introduced its services in the United States. To mark its debut, Cuttable is offering 1,000 ads to each online store in the country, totaling over 3.1 billion ads for Meta platforms such as Facebook and Instagram. The platform simplifies the creative aspect for online-selling brands by linking to their Shopify or ecommerce store and analyzing the products they offer.

data.title: NYC mayoral candidate Andrew Cuomo secures support from pro-crypto group Innovate NY, emphasizing his tech agenda in tight race.
data.description: A prominent organization advocating for digital assets, Innovate NY, has officially endorsed Andrew Cuomo for the role of New York City mayor. This endorsement comes in the midst of a closely contested race, with Cuomo's agenda focusing on blockchain technology and artificial intelligence gaining particular attention. The support from Innovate NY underscores the significance of Cuomo's approach, as he vies against other candidates for the position.

data.title: ServiceNow reports strong Q3 results, aiming to exceed $500M in AI ACV; Goldman Sachs raises price target to $1,250.
data.description: ServiceNow Inc, listed on NYSE as NOW, posted robust third-quarter earnings, potentially surpassing $500 million in AI annual contract value (ACV) by the end of the year, as per Goldman Sachs analysis. Analyst Kash Rangan maintained a Buy rating and raised the price target outlook from $1,200 to $1,250. ServiceNow's subscription revenue surged by 21.5%, beating the projected 19.5%, marking its strongest growth in the quarter. The company is demonstrating strong momentum. For more insights, check the full story on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Strong performance in Q3 2025 with revenue at $313m (+27% y-o-y) and adjusted EBITDA at $167m (+70% y-o-y). Net Cash Flow of $53m & $62m YTD.
data.description: Viridien reported strong third-quarter results in 2025, with segment revenue reaching $313 million, a 27% increase year-on-year and segment adjusted EBITDAs reaching $167 million, up 70% year-on-year. The company generated a Net Cash Flow of $53 million in the quarter and $62 million year-to-date by the end of September. Viridien's full-year 2025 Net Cash Flow target is $100 million, and they have begun approximately $50 million in bond buybacks. The company announced active liability management with partial bond redemptions in early October totaling $48 million. Sophie Zurquiyah, Chair and CEO of Viridien, highlighted the company's focus on major offshore projects and collaboration with leading energy companies as drivers of performance. Viridien's Data, Digital, and Energy Transition segment had revenue of $244 million in Q3 2025, up 31% year-on-year, while the Geoscience segment saw revenue of $108 million, and the Earth Data segment had revenue of $136 million. The Sensing and Monitoring segment had revenue of $69 million. The Consolidated IFRS revenue for Q3 2025 was $266 million, a 22% increase year-on-year. Viridien continued to actively manage its liabilities, obtaining loans from Bpifrance and executing a partial bond redemption to optimize financing costs and enhance future Net Cash Flow. As of September 30, 2025, Viridien had strong liquidity, including a $125 million RCF. Despite volatile oil prices, Viridien remains confident in its performance and strategic positioning in the market.

data.title: Insight Digital Partners II closes $172.5 M IPO with 17.25 M units, priced at $10 each, including underwriters' full option.
data.description: Insight Digital Partners II, a company listed as DYORU on Nasdaq, has recently completed its initial public offering. The offering included a total of 17,250,000 units, with an additional 2,250,000 units issued due to the underwriters exercising their over-allotment option in full. Each unit was priced at $10.00 and comprised one Class A ordinary share and half of one redeemable warrant. The warrants can be exercised to buy one Class A ordinary share at $11.50 per share.

data.title: Kroger and Uber Eats partner to offer more access and rewards; benefit customers nationwide. #Kroger #UberEats #partnership
data.description: In a joint announcement on October 30, 2025, Uber Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: UBER) and The Kroger Co. (NYSE: KR) revealed an enhanced partnership. The collaboration integrates Kroger's Family of Companies with Uber Eats' top-tier delivery service, simplifying the process for customers. This partnership aims to leverage Kroger's reach and Uber Eats' advanced delivery platform to enhance convenience for consumers.

data.title: Net at Work acquires LLB Partners to enhance consulting and support for Sage, Acumatica with widened capabilities.
data.description: A recent acquisition has strengthened consulting, development, and helpdesk services, enhancing support for Sage and Acumatica business applications. Net at Work, a prominent technology advisor in North America, announced this significant move on October 30, 2025. The acquisition is set to deepen their capabilities in these areas, catering to small and mid-size businesses. This strategic development marks a commitment to expanding their range of services and enhancing their support for clients using Sage and Acumatica applications.
